The paper deals with lossy compression of bit sequences, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm used, Codelet Parsing, is an extension of the Lempel Ziv algorithm, which is a well-known data structure (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the construction of codebooks, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). The use of the rate distortion function to measure the quality of the lossy compression is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the optimality of the algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
